    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>New snow and wind slabs in all aspects. New snow represents the main danger.</highlights>
      <comment>As a consequence of new snow and a strong to storm force northeasterly wind, sometimes large wind slabs will form by the evening in particular in places that are protected from the wind. In all aspects medium-sized slab avalanches are possible as a consequence of the snowfall. In particular on wind-loaded slopes the avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack and reach large size in isolated cases.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The old snowpack is largely stable. The new snow will be deposited on a quite favourable old snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
